Name: Aimee Kane
Comments: This is a great way to preview the program and learn about others' work. Thanks for involving us in the process.

Name: Andrea Wiggins
Comments:
Can't remember how many papers are usually in a session, but the last two on the list (digital mobilization and trustworthy by design) are both specifically speaking to data quality and data structures to support field practices, so they clearly fit very well with ours. Most of the other "okay" ones could fit well in a session together, as they're more generally about social structures in some inter-related areas, but would be fine complements to the three that obviously belong together.

I like this system, by the way. Nice preview of related work (so excited to see some of these papers!) and no one likes being stuck in a session where they feel their work doesn't fit in. Also, matching up crisis response and citizen science totally works because they're dealing with some very similar issues but in different contexts.
